The symbol * is used to replace the word "in" or the number "in." It is a shortcut notation that saves space and makes the text more concise.

For example, in the image, the line item "Atom Absorption Spectrometer" has the symbol * followed by the number 17.0. This means that the cost of the item is 17,000 dollars (or thousands of dollars).
